From 17819956a110f21f98337bd8fc7067433182e9d5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chwee-Lin Choong <chwee.lin.choong@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2025 10:40:22 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] doc: add example for IEEE 802.1AS-2020 multi-time domain with
 CMLDS

This update adds a new EXAMPLES section to the ptp4l.8 man page,
demonstrating IEEE 802.1AS-2020 multi-time domain operation with
Common Mean Link Delay Service (CMLDS). The example illustrates
how to:

 - Identify the PTP Hardware Clock (PHC)
 - Create and verify virtual clocks
 - Assign virtual clocks to separate gPTP time domains (0 and 1)
 - Launch CMLDS and ptp4l instances for each domain

Accompanying this documentation are three new sample configuration
files:

 - configs/gPTP_CMLDS_server.cfg
 - configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain0.cfg
 - configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain1.cfg

In addition, the README is updated to mention that 802.1AS-2020
support includes multi-time domain operation with CMLDS.

Signed-off-by: Chwee-Lin Choong <chwee.lin.choong@intel.com>
---
 README.org                     |  6 +++-
 configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain0.cfg | 39 ++++++++++++++++++++++++
 configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain1.cfg | 41 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 configs/gPTP_CMLDS_server.cfg  | 33 ++++++++++++++++++++
 ptp4l.8                        | 55 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 5 files changed, 173 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain0.cfg
 create mode 100644 configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain1.cfg
 create mode 100644 configs/gPTP_CMLDS_server.cfg

diff --git a/README.org b/README.org
index 3c33d64..c679315 100644
--- a/README.org
+++ b/README.org
@@ -28,7 +28,9 @@
 
   - Transport over UDP/IPv4, UDP/IPv6, and raw Ethernet (Layer 2).
 
-  - Supports IEEE 802.1AS-2011 in the role of end station.
+  - Supports IEEE 802.1AS-2011 and 802.1AS-2020 in the role of end
+    station. 802.1AS-2020 support includes multi-time domain operation
+    with Common Mean Link Delay Service (CMLDS).
 
   - Modular design allowing painless addition of new transports and
     clock servos.
@@ -45,6 +47,8 @@
 
     - The telecom profiles G.8265.1, G.8275.1, and G.8275.2.
 
+    - The IEEE 802.1AS/gPTP profiles, with and without CMLDS support.
+
   - Supports the NetSync Monitor protocol.
 
   - Implements Peer to peer one-step.
diff --git a/configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain0.cfg b/configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain0.cfg
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..1e75f85
--- /dev/null
+++ b/configs/gPTP_CMLDS_domain0.cfg
@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@
+#
+# 802.1AS CMLDS client for domain 0, example configuration
+# containing those attributes which differ from the defaults.
+# See the file, default.cfg, for the complete list of available 
+# options.
+#
+[global]
+#
+# Options carried over from gPTP.
+#
+gmCapable                 1
+priority1                 248
+priority2                 248
+logAnnounceInterval       0
+logSyncInterval           -3
+syncReceiptTimeout        3
+assume_two_step           1
+path_trace_enabled        1
+follow_up_info            1
+transportSpecific         0x1
+ptp_dst_mac               01:80:C2:00:00:0E
+network_transport         L2
+#
+# Options carried over from CMLDS_client.
+#
+delay_mechanism           COMMON_P2P
+#
+# UDS addresses
+#
+cmlds.client_address      /var/run/cmlds-client-0
+cmlds.server_address      /var/run/cmlds_server
+uds_address               /var/run/cmlds-domain-0
+#
+# vClock assignment and identity
+# NOTE: The value '4' below is just an example. Change this to 
+# match the (virtual) clock used by domain 0.
+#
+clockIdentity             000001.0000.000000
+phc_index                 4
\ No newline at end of file
